column2: Question
Do you think things in the nation are generally headed in the right direction, or do you think things are off on the wrong track?
In reference to Georgia specifically, do you think things in the state are generally headed in the right direction, or do you think things are off on the wrong track?
What is the single most important issue facing Georgia today?
Do you approve or disapprove of the way Joe Biden is handling his job as president?
Do you approve or disapprove of the way Brian Kemp is handling his job as governor?
Do you approve or disapprove of the way Jon Ossoff is handling his job as U.S. senator?
Do you support or oppose making betting on professional sporting events legal?
Should Georgia move the date of the 2024 Republican and Democratic presidential preference primaries earlier in the calendar year in order to give the state more prominence in this process?

Currently in Georgia if no candidate receives a majority of the vote in the general election, there is a runoff election between the two candidates with the highest vote share in order to determine the winner. Should Georgia eliminate runoff elections and make the candidate who receives the most votes in the general election the winner?
How confident are you that the November 2022 general election in Georgia was conducted fairly and accurately?
Would you say that recent changes to Georgia’s voting laws made it easier to cast a ballot in the 2022 election, harder to cast a ballot, or would you say there was no difference?
The state of Georgia currently has a budget surplus. In your opinion, what should the Legislature do with these surplus funds?
column3: Return the money to citizens through tax rebates
Increase state spending on things such as education and healthcare

column2: In recent years, Georgia has recruited electric-vehicle and battery manufacturers to open facilities in the state. Companies including SK, Rivian and Hyundai have promised more than 20,000 jobs in exchange for billions of dollars in tax breaks, land and other incentives. Do you support or oppose efforts to develop an electric-vehicle industry in Georgia?

Georgia’s abortion law bans most abortions after a fetal heartbeat is detected, as early as six weeks of pregnancy. Would you like to see the General Assembly make abortion harder to obtain, easier to obtain, or would you like the current restrictions to remain?
Should Georgia have a set of laws establishing minimum living requirements for rental properties so that they are safe, sanitary and fit for habitation?
Which of the following comes closest to your view of marijuana use by adults?

column3: Legal for both medical and recreational use

column2: President Biden recently pardoned individuals convicted on federal charges of simple marijuana possession. Do you approve or disapprove of these pardons?
